##Those verses from the Japanese donation

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

The Chinese poems on Japanese aid are an expression of support as well as friendship.
By Han Fenglan Min Yu Gan Li man Wu Minxia
Editor | Shen Xiaoshan

Recently, the anti-epidemic materials donated by Japan have attracted wide attention. On the outer packing of these materials, some classics have been quoted. In addition, there are "exotic mountains and rivers, same moon and same sky" from Prince Ket of Longhouse, there are also poems, such as the book of songs, taken from Chinese classical literature and rich in meaning and emotion, which express not only Japan's support for China's fight against the epidemic, but also the long-standing friendship between China and Japan.

The mountains and rivers are different, the wind and the moon are the same day

The Japanese Hanyu Shuiping Kaoshi HSK affairs bureau supplies Hubei Universities with the inscription "mountains and rivers, exotic places, wind and moon on the same day" .

In the 7th century, Buddhist Culture emerged from the Tang Dynasty and blossomed in a foreign land. Now, at the beginning of the 21st century's new decade, Cultural Comfort from Japan has given Wuhan a different kind of warmth.

More than one thousand, three hundred years ago, Buddhist Culture in Japan faced the dilemma of "spontaneity" , although "bring" Buddhism, but still can not play its real role. It was at this time that Prince Toneri went to the Tang Dynasty in search of a famous monk. "The mountains and rivers are different places, the wind and the moon are the same day. I send them to the Buddha and they are bound for each other. " The GATHA embroidered on the Cassock moved Jianzhen, and they crossed into Japan. On February 2,2020, ket language passed through thousands of years and became the witness of the friendship between China and Japan, touching the Chinese people in this spring.

Mountains and rivers are different, people are different, but we are under the same sky, a total Mu Qingfeng, with a bright moon. The donation of HSK to Wuhan University is the best wish for our Wishing We Last Forever. What is moving is not only the material help, but also the Japanese respect, recognition and inheritance of Chinese traditional culture, as well as the Japanese people's appreciation of the friendship between China and Japan.

Chinese and Japanese Culture "A strip of water" , Chinese Tang Dynasty culture is the Japanese culture has a far-reaching impact. In Japan, there are many people who love Chinese traditional culture. Nowadays, more and more Japanese universities offer Chinese courses, and folk Chinese teaching is becoming more and more active. In 2019, Zeng Zekong, the head of the Japan Youth Association, said more than 40,000 students would take the HSK test.

How shall it be said that you have no clothes ? I will share my lower garments with you 

Also attached to the poem are donations of medical supplies to Hubei from Japan's NPO Association, the Hubei Chamber of Commerce in Japan, Huobi Global, and joint-stock Company.

The other three poems all contain the words "mountain" , "river" and other natural scenery, but "is not a clothing, and son with the same robe" reveals a kind of passionate and generous morale.

ORIGINAL POEM:
How shall it be said that you have no clothes ? I will share my long robes with you . The King is raising his forces ; I will prepare my lance and spear ,. And will be your comrade !
How shall it be said that you have no clothes ? I will share my under clothes with you . The King is raising his forces ; I will prepare my spear and Lance ,. And will take the field with you !
How shall it be said that you have no clothes ? I will share my lower garments with you . The King is raising his forces ; I will prepare my buffcoat and sharp weapons ,. And Will March along with you !

The poem was originally a battle song from "no clothes in the wind of the Qin Dynasty" . It shows the unity of the army and the people of Qin and the spirit of patriotism. WHO SAYS WE HAVE NO CLOTHES? We wear the war dress with you.

At that time, Qin was located in the eastern part of present-day Gansu Province and Shaanxi Province. The Qin people were brave and good at fighting. As Zhu Xi once said in his book of songs, "The customs of the people of the Qin Dynasty, in general, uphold the spirit, have courage first, forget life and light death, hence their presence in poetry. " The rolling yellow sand stirred up by men and horses' hooves on the battlefield seemed close at hand, the high morale of the Qin people had to be breathtaking.

According to Zuozhuan, in the fourth year of the reign of Emperor Lu Ding (AD 506 BC) , the Wu army captured Ying, the capital of Chu, "stand on the court wall and cry, day and night does not stop, spoonful drink does not enter the mouth, seven days, Qin Ai Gong for the Fu "no clothes" , nine Dunshou sit, Qin Shi is out. ". To strengthen the morale of the Qin Army.

Today, though not used as an inspiration for soldiers to fight on the battlefield, the phrase "do you have no clothes? Do you wear the same clothes as your son? " has a different meaning. "Epidemic" at present, medical personnel, military personnel, like the military and civilian in Qin at that time, in this no smoke on the battlefield to fight the virus bravely, save lives. Japan with this poem to Hubei, or hope to inspire the people fighting in the front line, unity and fraternity, a common fight against "new crown pneumonia. ".

Liao River Snow Melt, rich flowers bloom; together with gas and branches, a total of hope for spring

The phrase was printed on a face mask box donated by Toyama Prefecture to Liaoning Province. On February 10,10,000 masks were shipped free by China Southern Airlines from Toyama Airport in Japan to Dalian, Liaoning Province, to support Liaoning's fight against the epidemic.

It quoted from the Southern Dynasty Liang Zhou Xingsi "thousand words, " "Kong Huai Brothers, together with Qi Lianzhi. Friends and points, cut and grind the rule. "

"Tongqi Lianzhi" refers to the brothers and sisters of one's countrymen. The general idea is that brothers should care for each other, because the blood of their parents is connected to them like branches of a tree.

Toyama Prefecture and Liaoning Province have maintained friendly relations of cooperation for 36 years since they established friendly relations between provinces and counties on May 9,1984. As Tang Yijun, governor of Liaoning Province, said in his speech, "Liaoning is an old industrial base of China, separated from Japan by a narrow strip of water and across the sea. In particular, it has a deep and long history of friendship with Toyama Prefecture. "

"I know there is an urgent need for masks, " said Yuichi Sakuri, director of Toyama Prefecture's General Policy Bureau. "people in Liaoning Province are facing difficulties and we will support them. "

Castle peak together with cloud and rain, the moon has been two township

The same emotional poem reads, "When Mountains are in clouds and rain, the moon has never been in two townships, " was also printed on a shipment of protective materials that arrived in Dalian on Feb. 9. The materials were donated by the Japanese city of Wuhe in Ky≈çto Prefecture.

This line is from Wang Changling's Song of the Tang Dynasty:
Yuan River to pick up Wugang, send you off without a scratch.
Castle peak together with cloud and rain, the moon has been two township.

When did Aoyama of both places share the same shade of clouds, the same dew, and the same moon? The poem creates various images through imagination, turning "far" into "near" and "two townships" into "one township" . It contains the profound friendship between two people who share the same heart.

On 8 May 1982, Dalian entered into friendly city relations with Maizuru. Over the past 38 years, the two cities have carried out colorful exchanges in areas such as economy, culture and education. The two seaports have helped each other and Maizuru has become one of Dalian's most important "relative" cities in Japan. Every year in May, during the Huai Festival in Dalian, a large number of Wuhe citizens visit Dalian.

The supplies were accompanied by a letter of condolence from Doddo, an honorary citizen of Dalian and Mayor of Maizuru. In the letter, Doddo, the city's mayor, expressed his concern for Dalian, his best wishes to the city's health care workers, and that Maizuru would continue to raise supplies for the city.

It is appropriate to use the phrase, "when the mountains are blue and the clouds are blue, the moon has never been blue" to express Maizuru's friendship with Dalian.

Not to mention that the mountains, the moon night, can lift the Wuhe city people to Dalian friends miss, on the one hand is the comfort of friends, on the other hand has been deep unswerving friendship, infiltration between the lines.

Poetry spread for thousands of years, such an excellent culture is worthy of our pride, the same, cherish the culture of friendly neighbors also worthy of our open-minded learning. More chilling than the lack of supplies is the discrimination against disease, and this cultural respect is enough to bring spiritual comfort. The epidemic may hold us back for a while, but the foundations of the culture remain, one day, we can Sudden Impact.

References: Sohu, Beijing News, Dalian News, thepaper.cn, Xicouzhu APP, ancient poetry and prose

Source | NANDU weekly
